cs.FL, cs.DM, cs.LO, cs.GT, cs.DS 

This paper deals with the accepting power of automata with storage, which is a topic in formal language theory (cs.FL). The paper specifically focuses on the context-freeness and semilinearity of languages accepted by valence automata, which are a type of automata with storage. This connects the paper to the sub-categories of discrete mathematics (cs.DM), graph theory (cs.GT), and combinatorics (cs.DS), which are all relevant to the study of automata and formal languages. Finally, the paper provides characterizations and conditions for certain types of monoids, which suggests a focus on mathematical structures and algebraic properties, further supporting the inclusion of cs.LO (logic in computer science) as a likely sub-category.
